org.tensorics.core.commons.operations

Interface Conversion<T,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the object which shall be converted
    R - the return type, i.e. the type into which the object shall be converted
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Function<T,R>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IterableBooleanConversion, IterableOperation<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    And, CodomainExtraction, IterableAverage, IterableRms, IterableSize, IterableStd, IterableSum, IterableSumOfSquares, IterableVar, Or, TensorChangeDetectionOperation, TensorExtractionOperation, TensorReduction, TensorWrappingOperation
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Conversion<T,R>
extends java.util.function.Function<T,R>
    An operation that converts one type of object into another.
